  "text": "for some constants K r,N,ω . Moreover the expansion is uniform in that for any r, N , there is an integer s such that if ω runs over a set of metrics which are bounded in C s , and with ω bounded below, the constants K r,N,ω are bounded by some K r,N independent of ω. Remark 1. We take a different normalization of Bergman kernel, so the expansion starts with order 0, other than order n as it appeared in ( [CITATION_1] , Proposition 6).",
